(secondQuint)Comparing Self Monitored Blood Glucose (SMBG) to Continuous Glucose Monitoring (CGM) in Type 2 Diabetes.

 This study involves the use of the following 2 glucose monitoring methods to measure your blood sugar (glucose) levels and help manage type 2 diabetes: 1.

 Self Monitoring Blood Glucose (SMBG): blood glucose is measured 4-7 times each day using finger sticks and an AccuChek Aviva blood glucose meter.

 2.

 Continuous Glucose Monitoring (CGM): blood glucose is measured continuously via the DexCom SevenPlus CGM device.

 This device has been approved for use by the U.

S.

 Food and Drug Administration (FDA).

